text.tspan: Female labor force participation rates by family benefits public spending, 2000 to 2015
The labor force participation rate corresponds to the proportion of the population ages 15 and older that is economically active. Family
benefits spending refer to public spending on financial support for families and children, such as child-related cash transfers, public spending
Data source: International Labour Organization (via World Bank); OECD (2016)
